HEADWORD: Brontotherium
<hw>Bron`to*the"ri*um</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ thunder + <?/ beast.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A
genus of large extinct mammals from the miocene strata of western North
America. They were allied to the rhinoceros, but the skull bears a pair
of powerful horn cores in front of the orbits, and the fore feet were
four-toed. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

